// useAutoSave
// Debounces and auto-saves content whenever it changes, tracking save status and unsaved changes.

Default debounce delay is 2000ms.
Original content is captured on first render (or when key changes) as the baseline for detecting changes.
Save errors are swallowed — callers handle error feedback inside their onSave callback.

FUNCTION useAutoSave(content, onSave, delay, key) -> { isSaving, lastSaved, hasUnsavedChanges }  EXPORT
  Manages state: isSaving, lastSaved timestamp, hasUnsavedChanges flag.
  When key changes (e.g. switching items), resets the baseline content, clears unsaved state, and cancels any pending save.
  Whenever content differs from the baseline, marks hasUnsavedChanges and schedules a debounced save.
  When content matches the baseline, clears hasUnsavedChanges.
  On unmount, cancels any pending debounce timer.

---

FUNCTION performSave(contentToSave)
  Sets isSaving to true, then calls the onSave callback.
  On success, records the current timestamp as lastSaved, updates the baseline to the saved content, and clears hasUnsavedChanges.
  On failure, logs the error but does not rethrow.
  Always clears isSaving when done, provided the component is still mounted.
